    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ee3a3fbd_217b5217",
        "filename": "common/gcloud/iam/client.go",
        "patchSetId": 11
      },
      "lineNbr": 252,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-10-10T01:03:12Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Strictly speaking we can \"compute\" it once, instead of doing this on each call, e.g.\n\nvar (\n  DefaultBaseURL \u003d \u0026url.URL{\n    Scheme: \"https\",\n    Host: \"iam.googleapis.com\",\n  },\n  ...\n)\n\n\ntype Client struct {\n  ...\n  BaseURL *url.URL\n}\n\nReparsing same constant over and over again seems wasteful. I acknowledge that it\u0027s not a big deal, so as you prefer. (Though with url.URL constant, code will be somewhat shorter too).",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 248,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 252,
        "endChar": 2
      },
      "revId": "183177108876b22e37a1e6db0b5907fe6173bd69",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b3f635f1_35f1781f",
        "filename": "common/gcloud/iam/client.go",
        "patchSetId": 11
      },
      "lineNbr": 252,
      "author": {
        "id": 1307247
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-10-10T18:31:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thanks for the suggestion. I adopted a hybrid solution: vars are defined and re-used in normal code flow whereas parsing still happens with the test flows so the tests don\u0027t have to create URL structures.",
      "parentUuid": "ee3a3fbd_217b5217",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 248,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 252,
        "endChar": 2
      },
